        <h1 class="display-4">How to use the Tetrominoes application</h1>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col pb-2">
                <h2 class="text-dark">Single Player</h2>
                <p class="text-dark">To play Tetrominoes, anyone can visit the Single Player page and click the start button.</p>
                <p class="text-dark">Once the game has began, pieces can be moved using the left and right arrows, pieces can change orientation using the up arrow, and peices can fall faster using the down arrow.</p>
                <p class="text-dark">One a row has no vacant slots, the row is cleared and the score is increased. Once the blocks hit the top of the game board, the game is over and the user is informed of their score.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col pb-2">
                <h2 class="text-dark">Multiply Player</h2>
                <p class="text-dark">To play multiplayer Tetrominoes, logged in users can visit the Dual Player page and create a dual chatroom if one does not exist or join an existing chatroom. From here you can speak with other users in the chatroom and start a 2 player Tetrominoes game.</p>
                <p class="text-dark">Once the game has began, pieces can be moved using the left and right arrows, pieces can change orientation using the up arrow, and peices can fall faster using the down arrow.</p>
                <p class="text-dark">The other player's game is visibile as well so you can see how both player's are navigating through the game.</p>
            </div>
